<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 29 at 12:40PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Jefferson County through 115 PM MDT...
At 1239 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Walkerville, or near Butte, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Boulder, Basin, Wickes, Jefferson City, Elk Park and Corbin.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
